{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require Coroners to record when a death resulted from using a prescription drug",
        "additional_details": "Coroners routinely list the cause of death as \u201calcohol/drug related\u201d. We want the Government to require Coroners to record details of prescription drugs people were taking at the time of their death and when prescribed medications played a part in a death. This would allow for accurate public records and statistics as well raising more awareness for safer prescribing practices.",
        "background": "Coroners are not currently required to collect details of prescription drugs people were taking at the time of their death or record deaths from prescription drugs.",
